The paper focuses on the intersection of human-centered design and explainable AI, with an emphasis on the social and interpersonal dynamics of AI systems. This suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) as the primary category. Additionally, the paper discusses technical advancements in AI (cs.AI), the sociotechnical nature of AI systems (cs.CYBER), and the need for interdisciplinary collaboration (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the importance of participatory design (cs.CSCW) in developing human-centered AI systems.
